02:06.833 --> 02:08.750
<i>and the fight for women's rights.</i>

02:11.625 --> 02:13.916
<i>That's how I understood
that it was us women</i>

02:13.916 --> 02:16.708
<i>who had to shape the future of humanity.</i>

02:25.750 --> 02:29.125
<i>But ideas are powerless
if they aren't put into action.</i>

02:35.416 --> 02:39.541
<i>That is why I decided
to conceive a child myself that would be</i>

02:39.541 --> 02:41.625
<i>solely and exclusively my own.</i>

02:43.416 --> 02:46.541
<i>As a physiological contributor,
I looked for someone</i>

02:46.541 --> 02:48.958
<i>who could never claim it as his.</i>

02:55.416 --> 02:57.833
<i>From my womb, a girl was born.</i>

02:57.833 --> 03:01.333
<i>A eugenic girl, the first free woman.</i>

03:03.208 --> 03:06.833
<i>I would like to point out that Hildegart
did not come to life by chance,</i>

03:07.375 --> 03:11.166
<i>nor by the simple animal desire
of her parents to conceive her,</i>

03:11.958 --> 03:14.833
<i>but as part of a perfectly-designed plan.</i>

03:15.916 --> 03:20.541
<i>She had to be a pure being
who would fight for a decent society.</i>

03:20.541 --> 03:23.125
<i>She had to be the woman of the future.</i>

03:27.208 --> 03:28.958
<i>She started talking at eight months old.</i>

03:28.958 --> 03:32.750
<i>By the time she was two, she could read.</i>

03:32.750 --> 03:34.541
<i>At three, she could write.</i>

03:34.541 --> 03:37.375
<i>At four, she was a certified typist.</i>

03:37.375 --> 03:38.875
Seven o'clock. Get up.

03:38.875 --> 03:42.083
<i>She was raised
according to strict eugenic parameters.</i>

03:42.083 --> 03:43.875
<i>She'd always wake up at the same time.</i>

03:43.875 --> 03:44.791
Get up.

03:44.791 --> 03:48.041
<i>Every minute of her life
was organized according to a plan.</i>

03:48.583 --> 03:51.791
<i>Her nutrition and hygiene
observed strict rules.</i>

03:51.791 --> 03:54.083
<i>She would always have
fruit and milk for breakfast.</i>

03:54.083 --> 03:55.250
<i>Her dinners were light.</i>

03:55.250 --> 03:58.708
<i>In order to improve
her competitiveness and endurance,</i>

03:58.708 --> 04:00.250
<i>she would practice sports.</i>

04:00.250 --> 04:02.625
<i>At eight years old,
she could speak six languages.</i>

04:02.625 --> 04:05.250
<i>She was fluent
in French, English, and Latin.</i>

04:05.250 --> 04:07.916
<i>And she could translate
from German, Portuguese, and Italian.</i>

04:07.916 --> 04:09.625
What is eugenics?

04:10.166 --> 04:13.875
Eugenics is the application
of the biological laws of heredity,

04:13.875 --> 04:15.500
that is to say, genetics,

04:15.500 --> 04:19.166
<i>in order to perfect
the human species and society.</i>

04:19.166 --> 04:23.500
<i>At 14, she began studying medicine,
law and philosophy at the university.</i>

04:23.500 --> 04:27.958
<i>At 17, with honors,
she became Spain's youngest lawyer.</i>

04:27.958 --> 04:31.250
<i>Hegel believed that,
